<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9200, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <para>Use the following chart to diagnose CLUTCH LINKAGE conditions.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Identify the specific condition.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Investigate possible causes of the condition.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remedy the condition.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For complete INTERNAL clutch adjustments, refer to GROUP 11 - CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master
                    Service Manual.
                </para>
                <table id="t1101001">
                    <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.25in"/>
                        <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="2.74in"/>
                        <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="2.99in" colsep="1"/>
                        <thead valign="bottom">
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Condition</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Cause</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Remedy</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody valign="top">
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Poor Clutch Release</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Incorrect pedal height.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Adjust the pedal height; refer to
                                        <hotlnk document="s11010k_5.xml" xrefid="hl1101003">CLUTCH PEDAL HEIGHT
                                            ADJUSTMENT
                                            <xref refid="hl1101003"/>
                                        </hotlnk>
                                        .
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>&#160;</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Faulty linkage set-up.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Check the linkage for damage contributing to poor clutch release. Replace
                                        damaged components. Clean, lubricate, assemble and adjust linkage.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Noisy, Rattling Clutch</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Linkage system is "frozen," needs lubrication, is excessively worn, or has
                                        parts missing (washers, etc.)
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Replace missing or worn components. Clean, lubricate, assemble and adjust
                                        linkage.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Frequent Adjustment Required</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Free travel less than 1/8 inch (3.2 mm).</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Adjust the free pedal travel; refer to
                                        <hotlnk document="s11010k_5.xml" xrefid="hl1101004">FREE PEDAL TRAVEL AND FREE
                                            TRAVEL CLEARANCE ADJUSTMENTS
                                            <xref refid="hl1101004"/>
                                        </hotlnk>
                                        .
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Slipping Clutch</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>No free pedal travel.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Adjust the free pedal travel; refer to to
                                        <hotlnk document="s11010k_5.xml" xrefid="hl1101004">FREE PEDAL TRAVEL AND FREE
                                            TRAVEL CLEARANCE ADJUSTMENTS
                                            <xref refid="hl1101004"/>
                                        </hotlnk>
                                        .
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>&#160;</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Driver may be "riding" the clutch pedal.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Refrain from "riding" the clutch pedal. Adjust the free pedal travel; refer to
                                        to
                                        <hotlnk document="s11010k_5.xml" xrefid="hl1101004">FREE PEDAL TRAVEL AND FREE
                                            TRAVEL CLEARANCE ADJUSTMENTS
                                            <xref refid="hl1101004"/>
                                        </hotlnk>
                                        . Refer to GROUP 11 - CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Chattering, Grabby</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Binding in linkage system; worn linkage components.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Replace worn components. Clean, assemble, lubricate and adjust linkage.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>and/or Erratic Clutch Operation</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Release yoke fingers and/or release bearing wear pads excessively worn.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Replace the release yoke or the complete clutch assembly. Refer to GROUP 11 -
                                        CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="1">
                                <entry>
                                    <para>&#160;</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Loose engine mounts.</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Tighten to specified torque; refer to GROUP 12 - ENGINE in the CTS-5000 Master
                                        Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
